page.title: 11Geoffrey Lives in Banwell
page.content: Around my house is a farm and my garden is so big it looks like it is my garden and someone else's. I usually play by myself because no one lives near me. I play tennis against the wall and cricket with my dad. I like to play tennis and cricket because I want to do them when I grow up. I usually have cornflakes for breakfast. I leave for school at 8.45am, I go by car. My favourite school dinner is chips, fish and tomatoes. I leave school at 3.30pm. I watch the video, television or play the piano before I go to bed. I belong to cubs and the Tuesday Club. I like going to them because we play good games, and have quizzes and prizes. I also like to see the cars flashing past, most of the time the cars sound like a tune from my piano.
